        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer4439694203" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer13982964636928873103">If u love philosophy, science, literature or spanish authors check this out LOL! Its an easy read! <br/><br/><br/>This was a Mandatory read for literature class LOL! Loved it a lot. Andres hurtado is such an engaging and relatable protagonist (for the most part…. Lol) Barojas style is simple concise and to the point (noventayochismo things &lt;3) but not any less skilled because of it. The plot is engaging and all the characters feel interesting and fresh, borrowing the philosophical ideas popular from the time i</span>
  <span id="freeText13982964636928873103" style="display:none">If u love philosophy, science, literature or spanish authors check this out LOL! Its an easy read! <br /><br /><br />This was a Mandatory read for literature class LOL! Loved it a lot. Andres hurtado is such an engaging and relatable protagonist (for the most part…. Lol) Barojas style is simple concise and to the point (noventayochismo things &lt;3) but not any less skilled because of it. The plot is engaging and all the characters feel interesting and fresh, borrowing the philosophical ideas popular from the time it was written and mixing them with the ideas of science and medicine in order to give a hard critic on both the metropolitan and rural spain of the late 19th century. <br /><br />Couldve done without the antisemitism though, that really is what weirded me out. Like i still dont understand the point of that. But apart from that, great book i wish more people apart from spanish students of bachillerato would read. </span>
  <a data-text-id="13982964636928873103" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


